Bridge Base Inc. President ^*BFred Gitelman^*N was fortunate to be one of the 52 players invited to this year's Generali. In this tournament each player has a chance to play 2 boards with each of the other players as his partner! Everyone plays the same relatively simple bidding system. Fred had the unusual distinction of finishing with a score of 50.00%, dead average, after 4 sessions of play!  Even though Fred finished this event exactly where he started it, he found the 2000 Generali Individual to be one of the most enjoyable events of his bridge career. Thanks to the World Bridge Federation and the local organizers for running such a magnificent tournament!

Geir Helgemo, a past winner of the Generali Individual, does not need much of an introduction as he is widely recognized as one of the very best players in the world. Geir is always a complete gentleman at the table and, as Fred found out in their 2 boards as partners, he is also a pleasure to play with. In this week's deal Geir demonstrates 2 of the reasons he wins so often - he is fearless in the bidding and he plays his cards like a magician. The defense was far from perfect in this week's deal, but Geir's opponents were both former World Champions. The deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.
